[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was detected in the libexif image‐metadata[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing library when running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. During execution of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m‐byte read overruns a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m‐byte heap buffer by one byte. The overflow is reproducible via the fuzzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness at its initial invocation of `exif_data_new_from_data`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A heap-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mout-of-bounds read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was flagged by AddressSanitizer. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode attempts to copy [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting exactly at the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulting in a single‐byte overread.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Failure location  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The crash occurs inside `__asan_memcpy` as called by `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `libexif/exif-data.c` at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m. The immediate caller chain is:  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_content [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. exif_data_new_from_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif_from_data_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:51[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer is allocated on the heap and immediately used to load EXIF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata entries.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The code issues a `memcpy` of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes where only [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes were available, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading one byte past the end.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The redzone markers from ASAN confirm the exact overflow location [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter the region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness simply feeds arbitrary data into `exif_data_new_from_data`; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit is not itself faulty but highlights a flaw in the parsing logic.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for further investigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m in `exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: verify buffer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize vs. data‐entry length before copying.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_content [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: examine how content lengths are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculated and bounds‐checked.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and exif_data_new_from_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: review the overall flow of memory allocation, length parsing, and data entry [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Any utilities or helpers that parse length fields from the input stream, to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirm they enforce limits consistent with allocated buffers.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  allocated by thread T0 here:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at malloc[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at operator new[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      … fuzzer driver …[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow occurs because `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can read beyond [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe allocated buffer when `doff + s > size`.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `exif-data.c`, around the original `memcpy` at line [0m[1;36m209[0m[39m, the patch wraps the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopy in a length check:  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```diff[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mentry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39m        [0m[39mentry->size = s;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            unsigned int len;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                len = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                len = size - doff;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            else[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                len = s;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            entry->size = len;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This change intends to clamp `len` so that `d + doff + len` never exceeds `d + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize`.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Upon rebuilding and re-running the same fuzzer test, AddressSanitizer still [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreports a heap-buffer-overflow at the updated location in [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, now at line [0m[1;36m221[0m[39m:  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address … READ of size [0m[1;36m16[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at __asan_memcpy[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:221[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      …[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region …[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:221[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log details and allocation site mirror those in the initial report, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the overflow persists even with the clamping logic in place.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The offset and size calculations around `doff`, `s`, and the originally requested[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation size in `exif_data_alloc`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other code paths populating `entry->size` or calling `memcpy` that might [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbypass or miscompute bounds.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The upstream logic in `exif_data_load_data_content` that determines `doff` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`s`, to ensure all branches are covered by bounds checks.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential assumptions in `exif_data_alloc` regarding the requested size `s` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversus the actual buffer boundaries.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s libexif code triggers an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrunning the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow occurs in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` during a `memcpy` that reads past the allocated buffer.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted to clamp the copy region to the buffer’s real size—using [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mem_get_size` and calculating a safe `len` before copying—but the diff [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluded line-number labels [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “[0m[1;36m163[0m[39m:static int”, “[0m[1;36m168.1[0m[39m:[0m[33m...[0m[39m”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m which are invalid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mC syntax. As a result, the build failed with a syntax error [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“expected identifier [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor ‘[0m[1;39m([0m[39m’”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and an implicit-function-declaration warning for [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A libfuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m feeds arbitrary data into [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during a `memcpy` of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes just past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy`  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content`  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → fuzz loop → `main`  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations:  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code calculates a data length `s` from the entry’s format and component [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount, then an offset `doff`, but does not prevent `s+doff` from exceeding the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens when `s + doff > size`, causing `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to read out-of-bounds.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrapped `exif_data_load_data_entry` in a clamp block:  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Fetched the buffer’s real size via `[0m[1;35mexif_mem_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->mem[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • If requested `size` exceeded `real_size`, reduced it.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Computed a safe `len` based on `doff` and `size`, logging and returning if `len[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Allocated `entry->data` for `len` and copied `len` bytes.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The diff inserted numeric labels like “[0m[1;36m163[0m[39m:”, “[0m[1;36m168.1[0m[39m:”, etc., rather than pure C [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compiler error at the modified lines:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:163:1[0m[39m: error: expected identifier or ‘[0m[1;39m([0m[39m’  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m163[0m[39m | [0m[1;36m163[0m[39m:static int  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Warning about implicit declaration of `exif_data_load_data_entry` elsewhere, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the patch disrupted the function signature.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Build terminated with errors; no further progress.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `exif_data_load_data_entry`, including how `s` and `doff` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare derived and where they originate.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The memory abstraction [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`data->priv->mem`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the correct way to query an input [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer’s size.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Related functions in `exif-data.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_content`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data`, `exif_data_new_from_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for similar boundary checks.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how data buffers [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare supplied.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any existing tests or code paths that parse MakerNote entries, as those carry [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcustom offsets.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer run of the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` against libexif revealed a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `libexif/exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer’s log showed a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer. To address [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis, the patch adds calls to a presumed helper function `exif_mem_get_size`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclamps the requested copy region to the actual buffer size, and adjusts the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation and `memcpy` to use the clamped length. After applying, the build fails [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat link time with “undefined reference to `exif_mem_get_size`” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand a DWARF error[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer report:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlen == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG,[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +               [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Tag data len is zero or out of bounds"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +    entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +    [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build log excerpts:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[35m/usr/bin/[0m[95mld[0m[39m: DWARF error: invalid or unhandled FORM value: [0m[1;36m0x25[0m[39m`  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Undefined reference: `exif_mem_get_size` in `exif_data_load_data_content`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Linker fails to produce `libexif.a` [0m[35m/[0m[39m shared object.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Conclusion: The new symbol `exif_mem_get_size` is not defined or exported in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe current libexif sources or build system.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definition and availability of the `exif_mem_*` API [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mem_get_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the codebase.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory allocation and tracking facilities in `libexif`, including how [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->priv->mem` is created, which functions are implemented, and whether the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelper for retrieving buffer size exists.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build system [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMakefile/autotools[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to verify that any new helper symbols, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif added, are compiled and linked into the library.  [0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered in libexif’s [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled from exif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when the fuzzer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfed a crafted input to `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow occurs while copying [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtag data with `memcpy` past the end of an allocated region.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe attempted patch replaces the original bounds check and unconditional [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a “clamp-and-copy” approach: it computes `len = [0m[1;35mmin[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, size - [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, returns early if `len == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, allocates exactly `len` bytes, and then [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` from the input. [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying this patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow continues to occur at the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated `memcpy` call in exif_data_load_data_entry, indicating that the patch did [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot fully address the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash log shows an [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read at address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is exactly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone byte past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace highlights a call chain:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39muses `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content`  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is reproducible by running the fuzzer with the same testcase; ASan [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maborts consistently on the buffer overflow in exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Original code [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimplified[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `exif_data_load_data_entry`:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"out of bounds"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      entry->data = [0m[1;35malloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patched code replaces it with:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned int len;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          len = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          len = size - doff;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      else[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          len = s;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlen == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"len is zero or out of bounds"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      entry->data = [0m[1;35malloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m log_no_memory; return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      entry->size = len;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch compiles and runs, but the fuzzer still triggers an ASan [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at the updated memcpy site [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow line [0m[1;36m224[0m[39m in exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPost-Patch Log  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The new failure backtrace again points to `exif_data_load_data_entry`, showing a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read just beyond the allocated buffer end.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation size printed in the ASan dump is still [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes, and the overflow[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that some paths still allow reading more data than allocated, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdespite the clamp logic.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFurther Investigation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review all callers of `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially [0m                    [2m                [0m
